nt expression and socio-pragmatics. Moreover, common themes across contributions point to crosslinguistic tendencies that underpin the conventionalisation of communicative patterns for coordinating interlocutors' attention, and to points of departure for further crosslinguistic exploration of how grammatical asymmetries can be explained in terms of prominence.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aAustronesian Languages.  aLinguistic Typology.  aMorphosyntax.  aPragmatics.1 aArka, I. Wayan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonohue, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Owen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Bethwyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Bethwyn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFang-ching Teng, Stacy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHemmings, Charlotte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMazzitelli, Lidia Federica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNæss, Åshild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNæss, Åshild, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchokkin, Dineke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVander Klok, Jozina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVander Klok, Jozina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZeitoun, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z978311